**Definition**
Layout widgets in jQuery Mobile are UI components used to structure pages, organize content, and create mobile-friendly layouts.

**Types**

* **Header (`data-role="header")`**
* **Footer (`data-role="footer")`**
* **Content (`data-role="content")`**
* **Navbar (`data-role="navbar")`**
* **Collapsible (`data-role="collapsible")`**
* **Collapsible Set (`data-role="collapsible-set")`**
* **Listview (`data-role="listview")`**

**Working**
These widgets automatically apply styles, padding, themes, and behavior to create structured mobile layouts. jQuery Mobile scans for `data-role` attributes and converts them into mobile UI widgets.

**Diagrams (text)**

```
Page
 ├── Header
 ├── Content
 └── Footer
```

**Advantages**

* Fast layout creation
* Consistent look and feel
* Touch-friendly UI components

**Disadvantages**

* Less flexible than modern frameworks
* Styling can become heavy

**Examples**
Header + content + footer:

```html
<div data-role="page">
  <div data-role="header"><h1>Title</h1></div>
  <div data-role="content"><p>Hello</p></div>
  <div data-role="footer"><h4>Footer</h4></div>
</div>
```

Navbar example:

```html
<div data-role="navbar">
  <ul>
    <li><a href="#home">Home</a></li>
    <li><a href="#help">Help</a></li>
  </ul>
</div>
```

**Short code snippets**
Collapsible:

```html
<div data-role="collapsible">
  <h3>More Info</h3>
  <p>Details here...</p>
</div>
```

**Applications**

* Structuring mobile pages
* Navigation bars
* Collapsible menus
* Responsive mobile layouts
